7", "name": "Teddy Blume", "qid": null, "roles": ["violin"]}]}, {"label": "Introduction/ Opening Remarks", "work": "Introduction/ Opening Remarks", "composer": "Unknown author of spoken text", "performers": [{"id": "57263", "name": "Bob Garrity", "qid": null, "roles": ["host"]}]}, {"label": "A Night in Tunisia", "work": "A Night in Tunisia", "composer": "Dizzy Gillespie", "performers": [{"id": "21175", "name": "Charlie Parker", "qid": "Q103767", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"]}, {"id": "21443", "name": "Walter Yost", "qid": null, "roles": ["double_bass"]}, {"id": "25463", "name": "Dizzy Gillespie", "qid": "Q49575", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "33897", "name": "Walter Bishop Jr.", "qid": "Q933192", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "44577", "name": "Cándido Camero", "qid": "Q83693", "roles": ["congas"]}, {"id": "49009", "name": "Roy Haynes", "qid": "Q448235", "roles": ["drums"]}]}, {"label": "52nd Street Theme", "work": "52nd Street Theme", "composer": "Thelonious Monk", "performers": [{"id": "21175", "name": "Charlie Parker", "qid": "Q103767", "roles": ["alto_saxophone"]}, {"id": "21443", "name": "Walter Yost", "qid": null, "roles": ["double_bass"]}, {"id": "25463", "name": "Dizzy Gillespie", "qid": "Q49575", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "33897", "name": "Walter Bishop Jr.", "qid": "Q933192", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "44577", "name": "Cándido Camero", "qid": "Q83693", "roles": ["congas"]}, {"id": "49009", "name": "Roy Haynes", "qid": "Q448235", "roles": ["drums"]}]}, {"label": "Body and Soul", "work": "Body and Soul", "composer": "Johnny Green", "performers": [{"id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington", "qid": "Q4030", "roles": ["conductor"]}, {"id": "25463", "name": "Dizzy Gillespie", "qid": "Q49575", "roles": ["trumpet"]}, {"id": "27235", "name": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}]}, {"label": "The Tattoed Bride", "work": "The Tattoed Bride", "composer": "Duke Ellington", "performers": [{"id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington", "qid": "Q4030", "roles": ["conductor"]}, {"id": "27235", "name": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}]}, {"label": "Duke Ellington Medley", "work": "Duke Ellington Medley", "composer": "Duke Ellington", "performers": [{"id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington", "qid": "Q4030", "roles": ["conductor"]}, {"id": "27235", "name": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}]}, {"label": "Lover, Come Back to Me", "work": "Lover, Come Back to Me", "composer": "Sigmund Romberg", "performers": [{"id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington", "qid": "Q4030", "roles": ["conductor"]}, {"id": "27235", "name": "Duke Ellington and His Orchestra", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}, {"id": "56192", "name": "Billie Holiday", "qid": "Q104358", "roles": ["vocalist"]}]}, {"label": "Selections (unspecified)", "work": "Selections (unspecified)", "composer": null, "performers": [{"id": "5674", "name": "Ahmad Jamal", "qid": "Q379613", "roles": ["piano"]}, {"id": "13979", "name": "Ahmad Jamal and His Three Strings", "qid": null, "roles": ["jazz_ensemble"]}]}, {"label": "Selections (unspecified)", "work": "Selections (unspecified)", "composer": null, "performers": [{"id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington", "qid": "Q4030", "roles": ["host"]}]}], "quotes": [{"speaker": "Roy Haynes", "qid": "Q448235", "text": "But I didn’t know them. You know what? Duke’s band – when I was much younger, it was the hardest thing to get close to. Even Sonny Greer. I didn’t get – Sonny Greer, late in life, we were very close. I used to go to his gigs. He lived near Michael’s. He would come over there sometimes to see me and see these pretty drums. He was always – you ever see the set of drums that Sonny Greer would have? Jo Jones used to call them the Empire State Building. He had drums on wheels. He had tympanis. He had his initial on every drum, S. G. I had a picture of it at home when I was a teenager. He had the chimes, for something. When – I guess it was 1952, when Louie Bellson was leaving the band. He had married Pearl Bailey. He was going to Europe, I think, for a honeymoon. So maybe a few nights before that we were playing at Carnegie Hall. I was with Charlie Parker, and Duke’s band was there. Joe Morgan was doing p.r. for Duke. He kept instigating to get me in the band. I was living at the Hotel President on West 48th Street, right in front of Mama Leone’s, at the time. Duke called me up there, and he talked a lot. He didn’t really say – ask me to join the band, but he talked a lot then. But that’s what he wanted. I would always meet him at a restaurant up in Harlem called Ma Frazier’s. He always would mention the fact", "caption": "1952 Carnegie Hall gig with Duke Ellington and Charlie Parker", "conf": "high", "first_person": true, "doc_title": "Roy Haynes — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Haynes-Roy/Haynes_Roy_Transcript.pdf"}], "featured_people": [{"qid": "Q379613", "id": "5674", "name": "Ahmad Jamal"}, {"qid": "Q343903", "id": "66568", "name": "Bill Crow"}, {"qid": "Q104358", "id": "56192", "name": "Billie Holiday"}, {"qid": "Q103767", "id": "21175", "name": "Charlie Parker"}, {"qid": "Q83693", "id": "44577", "name": "Cándido Camero"}, {"qid": "Q49575", "id": "25463", "name": "Dizzy Gillespie"}, {"qid": "Q4030", "id": "4806", "name": "Duke Ellington"}, {"qid": "Q1264406", "id": "17894", "name": "Duke Jordan"}, {"qid": "Q359783", "id": "124449", "name": "Frank Isola"}, {"qid": "Q724132", "id": "52564", "name": "Jimmy Raney"}, {"qid": "Q448235", "id": "49009", "name": "Roy Haynes"}, {"qid": "Q30587", "id": "9196", "name": "Stan Getz"}, {"qid": "Q933192", "id": "33897", "name": "Walter Bishop Jr."}]}